John H. ROETHEL, Appellant, v. THE MYERS REGULATOR COMPANY, Appellee. No. 7926. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Nov. 8, 1939. Dike, Calver & Gray, of Detroit, Mich., for appellant. No counsel appeared for appellee.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ARANT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the motion of appellant to withdraw and dismiss appeal without prejudice be and the same is hereby granted.
